**Q7: How do you test with Hilt?**

**A:** Two patterns. **(1) `@TestInstallIn`** тАФ swap a whole module with a test version:
```kotlin
@Module
@TestInstallIn(components = [SingletonComponent::class], replaces = [NetworkModule::class])
object FakeNetworkModule {
  @Provides @Singleton fun provideApi(): UserApi = FakeUserApi()
}
```
The test uses the fake, production uses the real. **(2) `@UninstallModules`** тАФ annotate a test class to disable a specific module and provide dependencies inline. **Instrumented tests** use `@HiltAndroidTest` on the test class + a `HiltAndroidRule` to trigger Hilt for the test Application. **Unit tests** don't need Hilt at all тАФ just construct classes with `Repository(FakeDao(), FakeApi())` manually. Hilt shines when you want to test integration with Activities/Fragments.
